     1                                  ; bootf.asm  FAT12 floppy bootstrap for protected mode image
     2                                  ; Version 2.0, May 1, 1999
     3                                  ; Sample code
     4                                  ; by John S. Fine  johnfine@erols.com
     5                                  ; edited by Jeroen van Bemmel
     6                                  ; I do not place any restrictions on your use of this source code
     7                                  ; I do not provide any warranty of the correctness of this source code
     8                                  ;_____________________________________________________________________________
     9                                  ;
    10                                  ; Documentation:
    11                                  ;
    12                                  ;   1)  Most of the documentation is in comments at the END of this file.
    13                                  ;   2)  Some is in the read.me file that came with this file.
    14                                  ;   3)  In the comments within the source code are several uses of {}, each
    15                                  ;       of these indicates a section of documentation at the end of this file
    16                                  ;       which applies to that part of the source code.
    17                                  ;   4)  The major way I reduced code size was to rely on left-over values in
    18                                  ;       registers and/or to initialize registers at points where doing so was
    19                                  ;       cheap.  To make that understandable, there are several lines beginning
    20                                  ;       with either ";>" or ";>>".  These lines describe the register contents
    21                                  ;       at that point in the code.  ";>" indicates that the value is required
    22                                  ;       by the next section of code.  ";>>" indicates that the value passes
    23                                  ;       through the next section unmodified and is needed later.
    24                                  ;    5) I made this code by modifying my bootp example.  If something doesn't
    25                                  ;       make sense here, maybe comparison to the other version will help.
    26                                  ;_____________________________________________________________________________
    27                                  ;
    28                                  ; Limitations:
    29                                  ;
    30                                  ;    For simplicity, I made several assumptions about the environment.  Some
    31                                  ; of those may need to be expanded in a future version.  Except for the first,
    32                                  ; they are all things that could be checked by a "SYS" program that installs
    33                                  ; this bootstrap.  In general it makes more sense (where possible) for a SYS
    34                                  ; program to check compatibility issues than for a bootstrap to check them
    35                                  ; itself.
    36                                  ;
    37                                  ;    If these limits are violated, this code simply bombs.  It does not check
    38                                  ; the limits nor display error messages.
    39                                  ;
    40                                  ; 1) Runs only on a 386+
    41                                  ; 2) The FAT structure must be the first thing on the drive (no partitions).
    42                                  ;    It just uses "reserved" sectors before the FAT, not "hidden" etc.
    43                                  ; 3) The sector size must be 512 bytes
    44                                  ; 4) There are less than 256 sectors per fat (safe, since FAT12 has less than
    45                                  ;    4096*1.5 bytes per FAT).
    46                                  ; 5) LBN of root directory less than 65536 (safe in unpartitioned FAT12)
    47                                  ;_____________________________________________________________________________
    48                                  
    49                                  
    50                                  	struc	BB		;FAT Boot block
    51 00000000 <res 0000000D>          		resb	0xD	;Things we ignore
    52 0000000D <res 00000001>          BB_clu		resb	1	;Sectors per cluster
    53 0000000E <res 00000002>          BB_res		resw	1	;Reserved sectors
    54 00000010 <res 00000001>          BB_fats		resb	1	;Number of FATs
    55 00000011 <res 00000002>          BB_root		resw	1	;Root directory entries
    56 00000013 <res 00000003>          		resb	3	;Things we ignore
    57 00000016 <res 00000002>          BB_fat		resw	1	;Sectors per fat
    58 00000018 <res 00000002>          BB_sec		resw	1	;Sectors per track
    59 0000001A <res 00000002>          BB_head		resw	1	;Heads
    60                                  	endstruc
    61                                  
    62                                  %define FLAT_CODE 8
    63                                  %define FLAT_DATA 16
    64                                  
    65                                  ; Offset where this image will be loaded
    66                                  %define BOOT 0x7C00
    67                                  
    68                                  ;>   cs = 0
    69                                  ;>>  dl = drive we were booted from
    70                                  
    71 00000000 EB3C                    boot:	jmp short start			;Standard start of boot sector
    72 00000002 90                      	nop
    73                                  	; resb	0x3B			      ;Skip over parameters (set by format)
    74 00000002 <incbin>                	incbin "bootsector.bin", 3, 0x3b
    75                                  
    76                                  start:
    77 0000003E FA                      	cli				       ;{0}
    78 0000003F 31C0                    	xor   ax, ax
    79 00000041 8ED8                    	mov   ds, ax           ; Make sure that the DS offset == 0 (some broken BIOS might do otherwise)
    80 00000043 0F0116[E47D]            	lgdt	[gdt+BOOT]	   ; Load GDT
    81                                  ;	mov	ecx, CR0		   ; Switch to protected mode
    82                                  ;	inc	cx
    83 00000048 66B901000000            	mov ecx, 1			   ; JvB: added, enables caching
    84 0000004E 0F22C1                  	mov	CR0, ecx		   ;{5}
    85                                  .5:
    86 00000051 E464                       in	al, 0x64		   ;Enable A20 {4A}
    87 00000053 A802                    	test	al, 2
    88 00000055 75FA                    	jnz	.5
    89 00000057 B0D1                    	mov	al, 0xD1
    90 00000059 E664                    	out	0x64, al
    91 0000005B E464                    .6:	in	al, 0x64
    92 0000005D 83E002                  	and	ax, byte 2
    93 00000060 75F9                    	jnz	.6
    94 00000062 B0DF                    	mov	al, 0xDF
    95 00000064 E660                    	out	0x60, al
    96                                  
    97                                  ;>   ah = 0
    98                                  ;>   dl = drive we were booted from
    99                                  
   100 00000066 B010                    	mov	al, FLAT_DATA	; Selector for 4Gb data seg
   101 00000068 8ED8                    	mov	ds, ax			; {2} Extend limit for ds
   102 0000006A 8EC0                    	mov	es, ax			; Extend limit for es
   103 0000006C 49                      	dec	cx			    ; Switch back to real mode
   104 0000006D 0F22C1                  	mov	CR0, ecx		; {5}
   105                                  
   106 00000070 8816[007C]              	mov	[boot+BOOT], dl	; Save drive number we came from
   107 00000074 BC0008                  	mov	sp, 0x800		; {1B}
   108                                  
   109 00000077 6631C0                  	xor	eax, eax	    ; Segment
   110 0000007A 8ED8                    	mov	ds, ax
   111 0000007C 8ED0                    	mov	ss, ax
   112 0000007E 8EC4                    	mov	es, sp			; Read directory at 800:0 {1C}
   113                                  
   114                                  ;>   eax = 00000000
   115                                  
   116 00000080 A0[107C]                	mov	al, [boot+BOOT+BB_fats]	      ;Number of FATs
   117 00000083 F626[167C]              	mul	byte [boot+BOOT+BB_fat]	      ;Times size of FAT
   118 00000087 0306[0E7C]              	add	ax, [boot+BOOT+BB_res]	      ;  Plus Sectors before first FAT
   119                                  					                        ;eax = LBN of Root directory
   120 0000008B 660FB73E[117C]          	movzx	edi,word [boot+BOOT+BB_root]	;Root directory entries
   121 00000091 57                      	push	di			                     ; used again later
   122 00000092 4F                      	dec	di			                     ;Convert to number of sectors
   123 00000093 C1EF04                  	shr	di, 4			                  ;  16 directory entries per sector
   124 00000096 47                      	inc	di
   125 00000097 E8DC00                  	call	read_sectors
   126                                  
   127                                  ;>  eax  = LBN of root directory
   128                                  ;>  edi  = length of root directory in sectors
   129                                  ;>  [sp] = length of root directory in entries
   130                                  ;>  esi  = 00000000
   131                                  
   132 0000009A 66678D2C38              	lea	ebp, [eax+edi]		      ;ebp = LBN of cluster 2
   133                                  
   134 0000009F 5B                      	pop	bx			               ;Root directory entries
   135 000000A0 31FF                    	xor	di, di			         ;Point at directory {1C}
   136                                  .20:
   137 000000A2 8D36[D87D]                 lea	si, [file_name+BOOT]		;Name of file we want
   138 000000A6 6631C9                  	xor	ecx, ecx
   139 000000A9 B10B                    	mov	cl, 11
   140 000000AB 67F3A6                  	a32 rep cmpsb		; Found the file?
   141 000000AE 741F                    	je	found			; Yes
   142 000000B0 80C115                  	add	cl, 21			; Offset to next directory entry
   143 000000B3 6601CF                  	add	edi, ecx		; Advance to next entry
   144 000000B6 4B                      	dec	bx			    ; Loop through all entries
   145 000000B7 75E9                    	jnz	.20
   146                                  
   147                                  	;Couldn't find file in directory
   148                                  boot_error:
   149                                  disk_error:
   150 000000B9 B8070E                  	mov	ax, 0xE07		;{3}
   151 000000BC CD10                    	int	10h
   152 000000BE B800B8                  	mov   ax, 0xB800              ; load screen offset
   153 000000C1 8EC0                    	mov   es, ax                  ;
   154 000000C3 B8584F                  	mov   ax, 'X'| 0x4f00         ; put red crosses on the screen
   155 000000C6 B9D007                  	mov   cx, 25*80
   156 000000C9 31FF                    	xor   di,di
   157 000000CB F3AB                    	rep stosw
   158 000000CD EBFE                    	jmp short $
   159                                  
   160                                  ;>> ecx   = 00000000
   161                                  ;> es     = 800
   162                                  ;> es:edi = Directory entry of file
   163                                  ;> ebp    = LBN of cluster 2
   164                                  ;> eax    = 0000????
   165                                  
   166                                  found:	
   167 000000CF 2667FF770F              	push	word [es:edi+0xF]	;Starting cluster of file
   168 000000D4 8B3E[167C]              	mov	di, [boot+BOOT+BB_fat]	;Size of FAT (in sectors)
   169 000000D8 A1[0E7C]                	mov	ax, [boot+BOOT+BB_res]	;LBN of FAT
   170 000000DB E89800                  	call	read_sectors
   171                                  
   172 000000DE BB0040                  	mov	bx, 0x4000
   173 000000E1 8EC3                    	mov	es, bx			        ; es = 0x4000
   174 000000E3 66BF00000C00            	mov	edi, 0x100000-0x40000	; {1D}{4B} One megabyte minus ES base
   175                                  .10:
   176                                  
   177                                  ;>>    ecx = 0000????
   178                                  ;>    [sp] = Next cluster of file
   179                                  ;>     esi = 0000????
   180                                  ;>>    edx = 0000????
   181                                  ;>  es:edi = Destination address
   182                                  ;>     ebp = LBN of cluster 2
   183                                  ;>      ds = 0
   184                                  
   185 000000E9 6631C0                  	xor	eax, eax
   186 000000EC 5E                      	pop	si			      ;Next cluster of file
   187 000000ED 89F3                    	mov	bx, si
   188 000000EF 81FEF80F                	cmp	si, 0xFF8		;Valid cluster?
   189 000000F3 7329                    	jae	eof			   	;No: assume end of file
   190                                  					    ;Yes: (c-bit set)
   191 000000F5 D1DB                    	rcr	bx, 1			;bx = 0x8000 + cluster/2
   192 000000F7 8B18                    	mov	bx, [bx+si]		;Get word containing FAT entry
   193 000000F9 7303                    	jnc	.11			    ;Entry is low 12 bits
   194 000000FB C1EB04                  	shr	bx, 4			;Entry was high 12 bits
   195 000000FE 80E70F                  .11:	and	bh, 0xF		;Mask to just 12 bits
   196 00000101 53                      	push	bx			;Save cluster after next
   197 00000102 57                      	push	di			;Save destination address {7}
   198 00000103 A0[0D7C]                	mov	al, [boot+BOOT+BB_clu]	;Size of each cluster
   199 00000106 89C7                    	mov	di, ax			         ;  (in sectors)
   200 00000108 4E                      	dec	si
   201 00000109 4E                      	dec	si
   202 0000010A 66F7E6                  	mul	esi			   	  ; Times cluster number minus 2
   203 0000010D 6601E8                  	add	eax, ebp		  ; Plus LBN of cluster 2
   204 00000110 E86300                  	call	read_sectors  ; Read that cluster
   205                                  
   206                                  ;>     ecx = 0000????
   207                                  ;>>    edx = 0000????
   208                                  ;>      di = Clustersize in sectors
   209                                  ;>     esi = 0
   210                                  ;>>    ebp = LBN of cluster 2
   211                                  ;>    [sp] = Bottom 16-bits of destination address {7}
   212                                  ;>> [sp+2] = Following cluster
   213                                  ;>      ds = 0
   214                                  ;>      es = 4000
   215                                  
   216 00000113 89F9                    	mov	cx, di			; Cluster size in sectors
   217 00000115 86E9                    	xchg	ch, cl		; Cluster size in words
   218 00000117 5F                      	pop	di			    ; Restore destination address {7}
   219 00000118 2667F3A5                	es a32 rep movsw
   220 0000011C EBCB                    	jmp short .10		; Loop until end of file
   221                                  
   222                                  ;>     eax = 0
   223                                  ;>     edx = 0000????
   224                                  ;>      bx = 0FF?
   225                                  
   226                                  eof:
   227 0000011E 9A1000FFFF              	call 0xFFFF:0x10	; JvB added: execute bootphase2
   228                                  
   229 00000123 BA009C                  	mov	dx, 0x9C00
   230 00000126 8EC2                    	mov	es, dx			;es = 9C00
   231 00000128 31FF                    	xor	di, di			;{1E} Address of page tables WRT es
   232 0000012A B610                    	mov	dh, 4096/256	;edx = 4096
   233 0000012C B90004                  .10:	mov	cx, 1024
   234 0000012F B007                    	mov	al, 7
   235 00000131 66AB                    .20:	stosd
   236 00000133 6601D0                  	add	eax, edx
   237 00000136 CD08                    	int	8			      ;{8}
   238 00000138 E2F7                    	loop	.20
   239 0000013A 66C1E802                	shr	eax, 2			;{4C} (first time only) 4Mb / 4 = 1Mb
   240 0000013E F6DB                    	neg	bl			      ;Done just one page?
   241 00000140 79EA                    	jns	.10			   ;Yes: do one more
   242                                  
   243 00000142 FA                      	cli				      ;{6}
   244                                  
   245 00000143 66B803C00900            	mov	eax, 0x9C003	;First page tbl pointer in page dir
   246 00000149 66AB                    	stosd				      ;{1H}
   247                                  
   248 0000014B B8FA07                  	mov	ax, (1024-3)*2
   249 0000014E 91                      	xchg	ax, cx
   250 0000014F F3AB                    	rep stosw				; Not dwords: Would take too many bytes of instructions...
   251 00000151 B803D0                  	mov	ax, 0xD003		;0FF800000 page tbl pointer
   252                                  
   253 00000154 66AB                    	stosd				      ;{1F}
   254 00000156 B4E0                    	mov	ah, 0xE0		   ;Page directory self pointer
   255 00000158 66AB                    	stosd				      ;{1G}
   256 0000015A B000                    	mov	al, 0
   257 0000015C 0F22D8                  	mov	CR3, eax		   ;Set up page directory
   258                                  ;	mov	eax, CR0		   
   259                                  ;	or	eax, 0x80010001	   ; Turn on paging and protected mode and WP
   260                                  ;	and eax, ~0x60000000   ; Enable caching&WB by clearing bits 29,30
   261 0000015F 66B801000180            	mov eax, 0x80010001
   262 00000165 0F22C0                  	mov	CR0, eax
   263 00000168 B110                    	mov	cl, FLAT_DATA  ;Setup ds and es
   264 0000016A 51                      	push	cx			      ;{5}
   265 0000016B 1F                      	pop	ds
   266 0000016C 8EC1                    	mov	es, cx
   267                                  ;	mov	fs, cx			; Added: Also set up fs and gs
   268                                  ;	mov	gs, cx
   269 0000016E 66EA000280FF0800        	jmp dword FLAT_CODE:0xFF800200		;Go
   270                                  
   271                                  read_sectors:
   272                                  ; Input:
   273                                  ;	EAX = LBN
   274                                  ;	DI  = sector count
   275                                  ;	ES = segment
   276                                  ; Output:
   277                                  ;	EBX high half cleared
   278                                  ;	DL = drive #
   279                                  ;	EDX high half cleared
   280                                  ;	ESI = 0
   281                                  ; Clobbered:
   282                                  ;	BX, CX, DH
   283                                  
   284 00000176 6650                    	push	eax
   285 00000178 57                      	push	di
   286 00000179 06                      	push	es
   287                                  
   288 0000017A 6650                    .10:	push	eax		;LBN
   289                                  
   290 0000017C 6699                    	cdq			;edx = 0
   291 0000017E 660FB61E[187C]          	movzx	ebx, byte [boot+BOOT+BB_sec]
   292 00000184 66F7F3                  	div	ebx		   ;EAX=track ;EDX=sector-1
   293 00000187 89D1                    	mov	cx, dx		;CL=sector-1 ;CH=0
   294 00000189 28D3                    	sub	bl, dl		;BX = max transfer before end of track
   295 0000018B 39DF                    	cmp	di, bx		;Do we want more than that?
   296 0000018D 7702                    	ja	.20		    ;Yes, do just this much now
   297 0000018F 89FB                    	mov	bx, di		;No, do it all now
   298 00000191 6689DE                  .20:	mov	esi, ebx	;Save count for this transfer.
   299                                  
   300 00000194 41                      	inc	cx		      ;CL=Sector number
   301 00000195 31D2                    	xor	dx, dx
   302 00000197 8A1E[1A7C]              	mov	bl, [boot+BOOT+BB_head]
   303 0000019B 66F7F3                  	div	ebx		         ;EAX=cylinder ;EDX=head
   304                                  
   305 0000019E 88D6                    	mov	dh, dl		    ;Head
   306 000001A0 8A16[007C]              	mov	dl, [boot+BOOT]	;Drive
   307 000001A4 86E8                    	xchg	ch, al		;CH=Low 8 bits of cylinder number; AL=0
   308 000001A6 C1E802                  	shr	ax, 2		    ;AL[6:7]=High two bits of cylinder
   309 000001A9 08C1                    	or	cl, al		    ;CX = Cylinder and sector
   310                                  
   311 000001AB 89F0                    	mov	ax, si		    ;Sector count
   312 000001AD B402                    	mov	ah, 2		    ;Read
   313 000001AF 31DB                    	xor	bx, bx
   314 000001B1 50                      	push	ax
   315 000001B2 CD13                    	int	13h
   316 000001B4 58                      	pop	ax
   317 000001B5 7306                    	jnc	.30
   318                                  
   319 000001B7 CD13                    	int	13h		;If at second you don't succeed, give up
   320 000001B9 0F82FCFE                	jc near	disk_error
   321                                  
   322 000001BD 6658                    .30:	pop	eax
   323 000001BF 6601F0                  	add	eax, esi	;Advance LBN
   324                                  
   325 000001C2 56                      	push	si
   326 000001C3 C1E605                  	shl	si, 5
   327 000001C6 8CC3                    	mov	bx, es
   328 000001C8 01F3                    	add	bx, si		;Advance segment
   329 000001CA 8EC3                    	mov	es, bx
   330 000001CC 5E                      	pop	si
   331                                  
   332 000001CD 29F7                    	sub	di, si
   333 000001CF 77A9                    	ja	.10
   334                                  
   335 000001D1 07                      	pop	es
   336 000001D2 5F                      	pop	di
   337 000001D3 6658                    	pop	eax
   338 000001D5 31F6                    	xor	si, si
   339 000001D7 C3                      	ret
   340                                  
   341                                  ; SEGMENT .text USE32
   342                                  
   343 000001D8 4B45524E454C202042-     file_name db 'KERNEL  BIN'
   344 000001E1 494E               
   345                                  
   346                                  ;  subField             location
   347                                  ;  ------------------   --------------
   348                                  ;  Limit[0..15]          0..15
   349                                  ;  Limit[16..19]         48..51
   350                                  ;  Minor control bits    52..55
   351                                  ;  Major control bits    40..47
   352                                  ;  Base[0..23]           16..39
   353                                  ;  Base[24..31]          56..63
   354                                  
   355 000001E3 90                      align 4
   356                                  gdt:
   357 000001E4 1700                    	dw 0x17           ; limit
   358 000001E6 [E47D0000]              	dd BOOT + gdt     ; offset
   359 000001EA 0000                    	dw 0              ; dummy
   360                                  
   361                                  	; hand-crafted segment descriptor: OFFSET 0, LIMIT 0xFFBFF, type code
   362 000001EC FFFB0000009ACF00        	flat_code_desc db 0xff,0xfb,0x00,0x00,0x00,0x9a,0xcf,0x00
   363                                  
   364                                  	; hand-crafted segment descriptor: OFFSET 0, LIMIT 0xFFFFF, type data
   365 000001F4 FFFF00000092CF00        	flat_data_desc db 0xff,0xff,0x00,0x00,0x00,0x92,0xcf,0x00
   366                                  
   367 000001FC <res 00000002>          	resb 0x1FE+$$-$   ; 2 bytes left :)
   368 000001FE 55AA                    	db	0x55, 0xAA		;Standard end of boot sector
   369                                  ;_____________________________________________________________________________
   370                                  ;
   371                                  ;  Build/Install instructions:
   372                                  ;
   373                                  ;  *)  NASM bootf.asm
   374                                  ;
   375                                  ;   I left out most of the error handling (what do you expect for 1B1 bytes).
   376                                  ; For errors which it does detect, it just beeps once and hangs.  Errors (and
   377                                  ; unsupported conditions) which it doesn't even try to detect include:
   378                                  ;   a)  Not running on a 386 or better
   379                                  ;   b)  Active partition is not a FAT16 partition
   380                                  ;   c)  Root directory is more than 608Kb long.
   381                                  ;   d)  kernel.bin more than 4Mb long
   382                                  ;   e)  Total RAM less than 1MB plus actual size of TEST.BIN
   383                                  ; Errors which it does check for include:
   384                                  ;   a)  C-bit set after any int 13h
   385                                  ;   b)  No active partition
   386                                  ;   c)  No "kernel.bin" in the root directory
   387                                  ;
   388                                  ;    If this were a partition boot, you probably could leave out the code of
   389                                  ; reading the MBR, and finding and reading partition boot.  Then you could
   390                                  ; add a few error checks.  As a test boot used from a floppy, it needs to
   391                                  ; do that extra work and you just shouldn't use it if the basic conditions
   392                                  ; aren't valid.  As part of a large multi-boot (another example I hope to
   393                                  ; document) it could be bigger than one sector.
   394                                  ;_____________________________________________________________________________
   395                                  ;
   396                                  ; {} Documentation connected to specific source code sections:
   397                                  ;
   398                                  ;{0}  I wasn't sure what to assume about the CPU state when the BIOS (or
   399                                  ; earlier boot) transfers control here.  Probably interrupts are disabled and
   400                                  ; DS=0;  But I didn't assume that.  Assuming that could save a couple bytes
   401                                  ; of code.
   402                                  ;
   403                                  ;{1}  Memory use:
   404                                  ;  {A} The boot itself is at 0:7C00
   405                                  ;  {B} The top of the stack is 0:800
   406                                  ;  {C} The directory and FAT are both read in and accessed starting at 800:0
   407                                  ;  {D} The image is read in, then copied to 1MB (physical)
   408                                  ;  {E} The page tables are built at 9C000 physical
   409                                  ;  {F} The image is mapped to FF800000 linear   			(originally it said 0xfff80000)
   410                                  ;  {G} The page tables are mapped to FFC00000 linear        (originally it said 0xfffc0000)
   411                                  ;  {H} The first 4Mb is mapped linear = physical
   412                                  ;
   413                                  ;{2}  Most of this code runs in "big real mode".  That allows the code to make
   414                                  ;  int 13h (and other) BIOS calls, but also to access extended memory directly.
   415                                  ;
   416                                  ;{3}  I left out most error checks, and just beep once for the errors that are
   417                                  ; checked.  That makes this code suitable for learning about pmode booting and
   418                                  ; for test use by pmode kernel developers.  To package with an OS as end-user
   419                                  ; boot code, you need to either take out some of this code or load from
   420                                  ; some larger place, and add some real error messages.
   421                                  ;
   422                                  ;{4}  One way you might want to reduce the work of the boot is to leave the job
   423                                  ; of enabling A20 to the kernel startup code:
   424                                  ;  {A}  Don't enable A20 here.
   425                                  ;  {B}  Load the image at 2Mb instead of at 1Mb.  (Only odd Megabytes are
   426                                  ;       unusable when A20 is disabled).
   427                                  ;  {C}  "shr eax,1" to convert 4Mb to 2Mb.
   428                                  ; Note that the current version has a minimum memory requirement of 1Mb plus
   429                                  ; size of the image.  This change would require 2Mb plus the size of the image.
   430                                  ;
   431                                  ;{5}  The first version of this code changed the value of segment registers
   432                                  ; directly after switching to pmode.  It worked on all but one machine that I
   433                                  ; tested it on (a 386).  On that machine, on the second switch to protected
   434                                  ; mode, the first segment register loaded got the right selector but a bad
   435                                  ; descriptor.  I have read that you need a JMP after to switching to pmode, but
   436                                  ; successfully written MANY programs without that JMP and seen many more
   437                                  ; written by others.  I guess there is a case in which a delay is required (the
   438                                  ; usual "flush the prefetch queue" theory doesn't fit the observed facts
   439                                  ; because I fixed the problem by changing "mov ds,cx" to "push cx", "pop ds";
   440                                  ; They each take only two bytes in the prefetch queue.
   441                                  ;   Further testing has shown that on a 386 you may need more than a short
   442                                  ; instruction worth of delay after switching back to real mode.  Any memory or
   443                                  ; I/O read is enough, so I rearranged the code to have at least one such read
   444                                  ; between a change of CR0 bit 0 and a write to an sreg.  The "jmp short $+2"
   445                                  ; that others recommend would work because it forces a true fetch access (on
   446                                  ; a 386 at least).  I don't use it because I don't want to waste two bytes in
   447                                  ; boot code.
   448                                  ;
   449                                  ;
   450                                  ;{6}  Most of this code doesn't care whether interrupts are enabled or not, so
   451                                  ; I never enable them after the initial cli.  BIOS's correctly enable
   452                                  ; interrupts DURING the processing of int 13h, if they need interrupts.
   453                                  ; Unfortunately, some BIOSs also enable interrupts on exit from int 13h.
   454                                  ; Interrupts must be disable for the switch to pmode, so another cli is
   455                                  ; required.
   456                                  ;
   457                                  ;{7}  Only the low half of edi is used by read_sectors, so the high half
   458                                  ; doesn't need to be saved and restored across that use.
   459                                  ;
   460                                  ;{8}  I call int 8 (IRQ 0) many times.  This is done in case the code was
   461                                  ; loaded from floppy.  It tricks the BIOS into turning the floppy motor off.
   462                                  ; I don't like to start my pmode tests with the floppy motor on.
   463                                  ;
   464                                  ;{9}  The first entry in a GDT is never used by the CPU.  A zero selector is
   465                                  ; defined as being safe to put into a segment register without loading a
   466                                  ; descriptor from the GDT (You can't access memory through it).  I generally
   467                                  ; use the first 6 bytes of the GDT as a self pointer.  Once you are used to
   468                                  ; this convention, it makes code more readable.  The macros in gdt.inc set it
   469                                  ; up.
   470                                  ;_____________________________________________________________________________
